Step 1: Copy & paste this code into your website:

<script type="text/javascript">
function mCAPTCHA() {
  var mCAPTCHA_digitCount = 8 /* change it to whatever you want, it's 8 on default */
  var number = Math.floor(Math.random() * Math.pow(10, mCAPTCHA_digitCount));
  var mCAPTCHA_input = prompt('This website is protected by mCAPTCHA 2.\nPlease, enter in the following number:\n' + number);
  if (mCAPTCHA_input == number) {
    alert('mCAPTCHA approved your input. Action unblocked.');
    /* insert function name here */();
  } else {
    alert('Incorrect! Action blocked. Please try again.');
  }
}
</script>

Step 2: Replace the insert function name here section with the function name
Step 3: Done! You have successfully added mCAPTCHA 2 to your website.
(mCAPTCHA 2 has been tested before release. If you find any bugs, put them on issues.)
